1
00:03:00,272 --> 00:03:01,689
Dad.

2
00:04:47,379 --> 00:04:51,633
Clear the ramp! 30 seconds!
God be with you!

3
00:04:51,717 --> 00:04:56,971
Port side stick, starboard side stick,
move fast and clear those murder holes.

4
00:04:57,056 --> 00:04:59,390
I want to see plenty of beach
between men.

5
00:04:59,475 --> 00:05:03,394
Five men is a juicy opportunity.
One man is a waste of ammo.

6
00:05:03,479 --> 00:05:05,563
Keep the sand out of your weapons.

7
00:05:05,689 --> 00:05:10,068
Keep those actions clear.
And I'll see you on the beach.

8
00:05:42,226 --> 00:05:44,435
Clear the murder holes!

9
00:06:00,786 --> 00:06:02,328
Over the side!

10
00:06:08,836 --> 00:06:11,254
Port and starboard, over..

11
00:07:20,449 --> 00:07:21,699
Jesus.

12
00:07:22,159 --> 00:07:23,910
Thank you..

13
00:09:42,800 --> 00:09:45,843
I said, what the hell do we do now, sir?

14
00:09:47,304 --> 00:09:50,515
Captain Miller! Captain Miller!

15
00:09:52,184 --> 00:09:55,353
- Captain Miller!
- Sergeant Horvath!

16
00:09:56,897 --> 00:10:00,566
Move your men off the beach! Go!

17
00:10:00,692 --> 00:10:01,984
Okay, you guys!

18
00:10:02,069 --> 00:10:05,154
- Get on my ass! Follow me!
- Sir!

19
00:10:05,531 --> 00:10:07,532
What's the rallying point?

20
00:10:07,658 --> 00:10:09,450
Anywhere but here!

21
00:10:22,548 --> 00:10:25,007
The seawall! Move up to the seawall!

22
00:10:25,092 --> 00:10:27,385
Sir, I'm staying!

23
00:10:27,469 --> 00:10:29,762
Clear this beach!
Make way for the others!

24
00:10:29,888 --> 00:10:32,431
This is all we got
between us and the Almighty.

25
00:10:32,558 --> 00:10:36,561
Every inch of this beach
has been pre-sighted!

26
00:10:37,437 --> 00:10:40,731
You stay here, you're dead men!

27
00:10:53,954 --> 00:10:57,498
Mama! Mama!

28
00:11:02,129 --> 00:11:04,630
Stay down! Stay down!

29
00:11:09,303 --> 00:11:10,636
What are you guys?

30
00:11:10,721 --> 00:11:13,431
104th Medical Battalion, sir!

31
00:11:13,515 --> 00:11:16,183
Here to set up field operations!

32
00:11:16,268 --> 00:11:17,810
Get rid of that crap!

33
00:11:17,895 --> 00:11:20,980
Grab yourselves some weapons.
Follow me.

34
00:11:28,572 --> 00:11:31,490
- I'm hit! I'm hit!
- Briggs!

35
00:11:35,746 --> 00:11:40,041
Get me out of here. I'm hit low. God!

36
00:11:40,125 --> 00:11:43,210
- Medic!
- Navy Beach Battalion, sir.

37
00:11:43,295 --> 00:11:47,006
I gotta clear these obstacles,
make holes for the tanks.

38
00:11:47,090 --> 00:11:49,425
All the armour is foundering
in the Channel.

39
00:11:49,509 --> 00:11:52,762
Orders, sir. You go somewhere else.
I'm clearing this one!

40
00:11:52,846 --> 00:11:54,639
Come on, Briggs!

41
00:11:59,227 --> 00:12:00,603
Medic!

42
00:12:37,683 --> 00:12:39,308
Move! Move!

43
00:12:46,984 --> 00:12:50,111
Move! Come on! Move!

44
00:13:11,883 --> 00:13:15,219
Shore party.
No armour has made it ashore.

45
00:13:15,303 --> 00:13:20,016
We got no DD tanks on the beach.
Dog One is not open.

46
00:13:20,976 --> 00:13:24,603
- Who's in command here?
- You are, sir!

47
00:13:26,231 --> 00:13:28,691
- Sergeant Horvath!
- Sir!

48
00:13:28,775 --> 00:13:30,818
You recognise where we are?

49
00:13:30,902 --> 00:13:33,320
Right where we're supposed to be,
but no one else is!

50
00:13:33,405 --> 00:13:36,866
Nobody's where they're supposed to be.

51
00:13:36,950 --> 00:13:38,534
Shore party.

52
00:13:39,327 --> 00:13:41,579
First wave, ineffective.

53
00:13:41,663 --> 00:13:45,708
We do not hold the beach.
Say again, we do not hold the beach.

54
00:13:46,084 --> 00:13:47,460
We're all mixed up, sir.

55
00:13:47,544 --> 00:13:49,336
We got the leftovers from Fox Company,

56
00:13:49,421 --> 00:13:51,380
Able Company and George Company!

57
00:13:51,465 --> 00:13:55,092
Plus we got some Navy demo guys
and a beachmaster!

58
00:13:56,636 --> 00:13:59,638
Shore party. Shore party.

59
00:14:05,729 --> 00:14:08,064
CATF, CATF..

60
00:14:11,568 --> 00:14:13,861
- Reiben here, sir!
- Did you see anybody else?

61
00:14:13,945 --> 00:14:16,739
- Jackson, but that's about it.
- Mellish here.

62
00:14:16,823 --> 00:14:20,076
Caparzo! We got deforest
back there with Wade.

63
00:14:20,160 --> 00:14:23,913
He's hurt so bad he says
he sprung 100 leaks.

64
00:14:23,997 --> 00:14:25,664
Wade says he's all used up.

65
00:14:25,749 --> 00:14:28,000
- Move on to somebody you can help.
- Let's go!

66
00:14:28,085 --> 00:14:30,544
He's battalion surgeon, sir!

67
00:14:34,591 --> 00:14:36,550
- Get his attention.
- Wade!

68
00:14:36,635 --> 00:14:38,135
- Yo, Doc!
- Wade!

69
00:14:38,220 --> 00:14:41,388
- Wade! Wade! Wade!
- Wade!

70
00:14:42,432 --> 00:14:45,726
- Wade! Wade! Wade!
- Too risky, Doc. Too risky.

71
00:14:47,187 --> 00:14:49,271
- Wade!
- All right. Get him off the beach.

72
00:14:49,356 --> 00:14:53,109
I got it! We stopped the bleeding!
We stopped the bleeding!

73
00:14:54,653 --> 00:14:56,278
Fuck!

74
00:14:56,363 --> 00:14:59,657
Just give us a fucking chance,
you son of a bitch!

75
00:14:59,741 --> 00:15:02,159
- Son of a fucking cocksucker!
- Wade! Come on. Come on.

76
00:15:02,244 --> 00:15:05,454
Wade! It's Mellish! Wade!

77
00:15:05,997 --> 00:15:07,665
- Mellish!
- Let's go!

78
00:15:07,749 --> 00:15:08,916
We found Miller!

79
00:15:09,000 --> 00:15:11,585
- Fuck it!
- Let's move! Let's move!

80
00:15:18,635 --> 00:15:21,762
This is all? This is all that's made it?

81
00:15:21,847 --> 00:15:25,349
We got scattered pretty bad, sir.
There's bound to be more.

82
00:15:26,351 --> 00:15:28,686
- Not enough. It's not enough.
- Dog One exit..

83
00:15:28,770 --> 00:15:30,146
It's gotta be that cut on the right.

84
00:15:30,230 --> 00:15:32,731
- Or is that one on the left? Shit!
- No. No, no, no.

85
00:15:32,816 --> 00:15:35,526
Vierville is to the west of us.
This is Dog One.

86
00:15:35,610 --> 00:15:36,861
They're killing us!

87
00:15:36,945 --> 00:15:41,073
And we don't have a fucking chance,
and that ain't fair!

88
00:15:41,158 --> 00:15:45,452
Gather weapons and ammo!

89
00:15:45,537 --> 00:15:48,622
Come on, let's drag them in
off the sand!

90
00:15:56,715 --> 00:16:00,634
Reiben. Hey, Reiben, Reiben, Reiben,
where's your BAR?

91
00:16:01,386 --> 00:16:03,512
Bottom of the channel, sir.
The bitch tried to drown me.

92
00:16:03,597 --> 00:16:05,472
Find a replacement.

93
00:16:07,517 --> 00:16:10,477
Bangalores! Bring up some bangalores!

94
00:16:11,897 --> 00:16:15,441
Grenades, grenades! Get me
some grenades. Get them over here!

95
00:16:18,111 --> 00:16:22,114
Bangalores up the line!
Bangalores up the line!

96
00:16:22,199 --> 00:16:24,491
Heads up! Bangers coming your way!

97
00:16:24,576 --> 00:16:26,994
Come on, come on, come on!

98
00:16:27,078 --> 00:16:29,914
- Jackson here, sir!
- Reiben back, sir!

99
00:16:30,582 --> 00:16:33,334
Oh, my God!

100
00:16:36,338 --> 00:16:38,797
One more. Give me one more.

101
00:16:44,137 --> 00:16:46,847
Oh, my God, it hurts! I'm gonna die!

102
00:16:46,932 --> 00:16:50,893
Oh, my God! Oh, Jesus! Oh, my God!

103
00:16:52,020 --> 00:16:55,439
Keep it moving. Keep it moving.
Almost got it.

104
00:16:55,523 --> 00:16:58,567
- Jesus! Lucky bastard.
- Come on.

105
00:16:59,444 --> 00:17:01,737
- Move it!
- Keep it moving. You got it?

106
00:17:01,821 --> 00:17:04,865
God! God, help me!

107
00:17:05,492 --> 00:17:07,409
You're not gonna die.
You're not gonna die.

108
00:17:07,494 --> 00:17:10,663
You're fine. Don't look at it.
Don't look at it.

109
00:17:10,747 --> 00:17:14,500
Bangalores! Clear the shingle!

110
00:17:14,584 --> 00:17:17,253
- Fire in the hole!
- Fire in the hole!

111
00:17:17,337 --> 00:17:22,800
Fire in the hole!

112
00:17:32,394 --> 00:17:36,105
We're in business! Defilade!
Other side of the hole!

113
00:17:49,160 --> 00:17:51,495
That's it! Let's go!

114
00:17:54,958 --> 00:17:57,084
Inspected. Morphine.

115
00:17:59,963 --> 00:18:01,338
Routine.

116
00:18:07,345 --> 00:18:08,804
Priority.

117
00:18:12,809 --> 00:18:14,018
He's gone.

118
00:18:26,448 --> 00:18:28,198
Son of a..

119
00:18:28,950 --> 00:18:31,618
- Get in there.
- Fuck. I can't move.

120
00:18:31,703 --> 00:18:32,953
- Mellish.
- Yes, sir.

121
00:18:33,038 --> 00:18:34,872
Give me your bayonet.

122
00:18:55,060 --> 00:18:58,812
Two MG42s and two mortars.
Add 20, left 30.

123
00:19:01,900 --> 00:19:04,651
There's a little defilade over there,
but it's the perfect fire position

124
00:19:04,736 --> 00:19:06,487
if we get some goddamn armour
on the beach.

125
00:19:06,571 --> 00:19:09,656
We gotta open up this draw!
We gotta get this draw open.

126
00:19:09,741 --> 00:19:11,658
Reiben, Mellish, let's get into the war!

127
00:19:11,743 --> 00:19:14,745
Grab some cover
and put some fire on that crew.

128
00:19:14,829 --> 00:19:18,540
Davis, Debernardo,
Young, Valk, get ready.

129
00:19:20,877 --> 00:19:22,586
Covering fire!

130
00:19:25,924 --> 00:19:27,633
Go, go, go!

131
00:19:41,648 --> 00:19:43,607
Goddamn firing squad.

132
00:19:43,733 --> 00:19:46,902
It's the only way we can get
everybody the hell out of here.

133
00:19:46,986 --> 00:19:51,198
Short, Payton, McDonald, Parkes!
You're next!

134
00:19:51,282 --> 00:19:53,909
Why don't we just hand out
blindfolds, Cap?

135
00:19:53,993 --> 00:19:55,577
All we can do here is die.

136
00:19:55,662 --> 00:19:57,246
Covering fire!

137
00:19:59,749 --> 00:20:01,500
Go, go, go!

138
00:20:02,752 --> 00:20:04,461
Come on! Come on! Come on!

139
00:20:04,587 --> 00:20:06,463
Go, God damn it!

140
00:20:18,810 --> 00:20:21,478
- Jackson.
- Sir.

141
00:20:22,689 --> 00:20:24,273
- Do you see that impact crater?
- Yes, sir.

142
00:20:24,357 --> 00:20:26,733
That should give you complete defilade
from that machine-gun position.

143
00:20:26,818 --> 00:20:28,694
Get in there and give me
some fire discipline.

144
00:20:28,820 --> 00:20:30,696
Wait for my command.

145
00:20:36,453 --> 00:20:37,828
Go!

146
00:20:48,882 --> 00:20:52,176
Captain, if your mother saw you do that,
she'd be very upset.

147
00:20:52,302 --> 00:20:54,553
I thought you were my mother.

148
00:20:55,388 --> 00:20:58,140
Be not thou far from me, O Lord.

149
00:21:02,687 --> 00:21:06,690
O my God, I am heartily sorry
for having offended thee.

150
00:21:07,901 --> 00:21:10,152
I detest my sins
for having offended thee, O Lord.

151
00:21:10,236 --> 00:21:11,778
I detest my sins for having
offended thee, O Lord.

152
00:21:11,863 --> 00:21:13,906
Listen to me, Lord.

153
00:21:19,162 --> 00:21:22,748
All my strength, haste thee to help me.

154
00:21:38,556 --> 00:21:43,560
- Dog One exit! Right here!
- We're in business!

155
00:21:45,104 --> 00:21:46,939
Move! Move!

156
00:22:28,273 --> 00:22:29,898
- Reiben.
- Let's go, Sarge. Go!

157
00:22:29,983 --> 00:22:31,275
Reiben.

158
00:22:56,134 --> 00:22:58,594
The place is full of 'em!

159
00:23:00,138 --> 00:23:01,805
Come on, Doyle!

160
00:23:03,308 --> 00:23:04,725
Sarge?

161
00:23:10,064 --> 00:23:13,150
- Flame!
- Doyle, do it!

162
00:23:17,655 --> 00:23:20,324
Don't shoot! Let them burn!

163
00:23:42,305 --> 00:23:45,599
I'll give you "comrade,"
you son of a bitch!

164
00:23:45,683 --> 00:23:47,351
Lie down!

165
00:24:15,546 --> 00:24:18,048
Cease fire! Cease fire!

166
00:24:18,132 --> 00:24:21,301
Cut it out! Cut it out! Cease fire!

167
00:24:22,387 --> 00:24:24,054
Sugar Cane. Sugar Charlie 3.

168
00:24:24,180 --> 00:24:27,391
Say again, Dog One is open.
Send in the dozers.

169
00:24:27,517 --> 00:24:30,560
I'm waiting for you
to tie in my flanks. Over.

170
00:24:31,562 --> 00:24:33,063
What?

171
00:24:35,650 --> 00:24:38,985
What? I'm sorry, I can't understand
what you're saying.

172
00:24:46,911 --> 00:24:49,496
What did he say? What did he say?

173
00:24:49,580 --> 00:24:52,749
"Look, I washed for supper."

174
00:24:57,380 --> 00:24:58,880
God damn it!

175
00:25:05,263 --> 00:25:06,847
- Hey, Fish.
- Yeah?

176
00:25:06,931 --> 00:25:09,599
Look at this. A Hitler Youth knife.

177
00:25:11,102 --> 00:25:14,271
And now
it's a Shabbat challah cutter, right?

178
00:25:24,198 --> 00:25:25,866
Keep it moving!

179
00:26:26,052 --> 00:26:27,928
That's quite a view.

180
00:26:28,888 --> 00:26:30,430
Yes, it is.

181
00:26:32,141 --> 00:26:33,683
Quite a view.

182
00:28:08,487 --> 00:28:10,655
"Dear Mr Brian Boyd,"

183
00:28:10,740 --> 00:28:12,908
"no doubt by now you have
received full information.."

184
00:28:12,992 --> 00:28:15,201
- "Dear Mrs Jensen.."
- "..untimely death of your son."

185
00:28:15,286 --> 00:28:17,203
"..no words of mine
can ever relieve the grief.."

186
00:28:17,288 --> 00:28:19,581
"Our outfit has felt his loss
tremendously."

187
00:28:19,665 --> 00:28:22,417
"He was a fine soldier
and he believed very strongly in.."

188
00:28:22,501 --> 00:28:25,211
"It's no secret any more
that we were involved"

189
00:28:25,296 --> 00:28:27,380
"in one of the most important
operations of this war."

190
00:28:27,465 --> 00:28:30,008
"Al was the one
who held us all together."

191
00:28:30,092 --> 00:28:31,343
"He was always the first to volunteer.."

192
00:28:31,427 --> 00:28:35,055
"..came to a clearing near a road
where over 4,000 troops had passed.."

193
00:28:35,139 --> 00:28:37,349
"Your husband served in a combat unit"

194
00:28:37,433 --> 00:28:39,976
"whose dangerous duty
is to place itself.."

195
00:28:40,061 --> 00:28:43,188
"..which we all cherish
and hold so dear."

196
00:28:43,272 --> 00:28:46,983
"The loss of Lee and others like him
is a distinct blow to the regiment."

197
00:28:47,068 --> 00:28:48,360
"I fully understand your desire"

198
00:28:48,444 --> 00:28:51,112
"to learn as much as possible
regarding the circumstances"

199
00:28:51,197 --> 00:28:53,323
"leding to his death."

200
00:29:45,501 --> 00:29:47,252
Colonel, I've got something
you should know about.

201
00:29:47,336 --> 00:29:48,628
Yes.

202
00:29:50,631 --> 00:29:53,174
These two men died in Normandy.

203
00:29:53,801 --> 00:29:56,636
This one at Omaha Beach.

204
00:29:56,721 --> 00:30:00,181
- Sean Ryan.
- This man at Utah.

205
00:30:01,851 --> 00:30:03,560
Peter Ryan.

206
00:30:07,314 --> 00:30:10,400
This man was killed
last week in New Guinea.

207
00:30:13,154 --> 00:30:15,572
Daniel Ryan.

208
00:30:16,282 --> 00:30:18,199
The three men are brothers, sir.

209
00:30:18,284 --> 00:30:19,743
I've just learned that, this afternoon,

210
00:30:19,827 --> 00:30:23,621
their mother is going
to be getting all three telegrams.

211
00:30:26,584 --> 00:30:28,835
That's not all. There's a fourth brother.
The youngest.

212
00:30:28,919 --> 00:30:30,920
He parachuted in
with the 101 st Airborne,

213
00:30:31,005 --> 00:30:32,464
night before the invasion.

214
00:30:32,548 --> 00:30:34,382
He's somewhere in Normandy.
We don't know where.

215
00:30:34,467 --> 00:30:36,885
- Is he alive?
- We don't know.

216
00:30:41,057 --> 00:30:42,682
Come with me.

217
00:32:26,495 --> 00:32:28,872
God damn it.

218
00:32:29,707 --> 00:32:31,541
All four of them
were in the same company

219
00:32:31,625 --> 00:32:33,626
in the 29th Division,
but we split them up

220
00:32:33,711 --> 00:32:35,503
after the Sullivan brothers died
on the Juneau.

221
00:32:37,506 --> 00:32:39,340
Any contact with the fourth son, James?

222
00:32:39,425 --> 00:32:43,386
No, sir. He was dropped about
15 miles inland near Neuville.

223
00:32:43,470 --> 00:32:44,762
But that's still deep
behind German lines.

224
00:32:44,847 --> 00:32:47,056
Now, Mac,
there is no way you can know

225
00:32:47,141 --> 00:32:50,059
where in the hell he was dropped.

226
00:32:50,144 --> 00:32:52,103
General, first reports out of
Ike's people at SHAEF

227
00:32:52,188 --> 00:32:54,063
said the 101 st is scattered
all to hell and gone.

228
00:32:54,148 --> 00:32:56,524
There's misdrops all over Normandy.

229
00:32:56,609 --> 00:32:59,527
Now, assuming Private Ryan
even survived the jump,

230
00:32:59,612 --> 00:33:01,070
he could be anywhere.

231
00:33:01,155 --> 00:33:03,198
In fact, he's probably KIA.

232
00:33:03,282 --> 00:33:06,951
And frankly, sir, we go sending
some sort of rescue mission,

233
00:33:07,036 --> 00:33:09,621
flathatting throughout swarms
of German reinforcements

234
00:33:09,705 --> 00:33:13,541
all along our axis of advance,
they're gonna be KIA, too.

235
00:33:36,065 --> 00:33:38,107
I have a letter here,

236
00:33:39,485 --> 00:33:43,571
written a long time ago
to a Mrs Bixby in Boston.

237
00:33:43,656 --> 00:33:45,573
So bear with me.

238
00:33:48,410 --> 00:33:49,953
"Dear Madam,"

239
00:33:50,663 --> 00:33:52,914
"I have been shown in the files
of the War Department"

240
00:33:52,998 --> 00:33:56,751
"a statement of the Adjutant
General of Massachusetts"

241
00:33:56,835 --> 00:34:00,171
"that you are the mother of five"

242
00:34:03,175 --> 00:34:06,886
"sons who have died gloriously
on the field of battle."

243
00:34:09,556 --> 00:34:13,309
"I feel how weak and fruitless
must be any words of mine"

244
00:34:14,103 --> 00:34:17,480
"that would attempt
to beguile you from the grief"

245
00:34:17,898 --> 00:34:20,316
"of a loss so overwhelming."

246
00:34:22,152 --> 00:34:24,153
"But I cannot refrain
from tendering to you"

247
00:34:24,238 --> 00:34:27,407
"the consolation that may be found"

