01:07:20,671 --> 01:07:23,172
between the mission and the men.

729
01:07:23,632 --> 01:07:26,717
Except this time, the mission is a man.

730
01:07:30,013 --> 01:07:32,473
This Ryan better be worth it.

731
01:07:35,477 --> 01:07:38,271
He'd better go home,
cure some disease,

732
01:07:38,355 --> 01:07:41,857
or invent a longer-lasting
light bulb or something.

733
01:07:42,651 --> 01:07:44,360
'Cause the truth is
I wouldn't trade 10 Ryans

734
01:07:44,444 --> 01:07:47,238
for one Vecchio or one Caparzo.

735
01:07:47,322 --> 01:07:48,656
Amen.

736
01:07:51,034 --> 01:07:53,160
Look. There it goes again.

737
01:07:54,204 --> 01:07:57,164
Sir, are you all right?

738
01:08:02,421 --> 01:08:05,715
Now, look, we're gonna
move out in two hours.

739
01:08:05,799 --> 01:08:08,092
Why don't you get some sleep?

740
01:08:08,176 --> 01:08:11,220
- I don't know how he does it.
- What's that?

741
01:08:11,305 --> 01:08:13,973
Falls asleep like that.
I mean, look at him.

742
01:08:14,057 --> 01:08:17,101
The guy's lights out the minute
his head hits the pack.

743
01:08:17,185 --> 01:08:18,769
Clear conscience.

744
01:08:18,854 --> 01:08:20,438
Yeah. What's that saying?

745
01:08:20,522 --> 01:08:23,691
"If God's on our side,
who the hell could be on theirs?"

746
01:08:23,775 --> 01:08:26,360
"If God be for us,
who could be against us?"

747
01:08:26,445 --> 01:08:28,571
Yeah, what did I say?

748
01:08:28,655 --> 01:08:32,908
Well, actually, the trick to falling
asleep is trying to stay awake.

749
01:08:32,993 --> 01:08:34,785
How is that, Wade?

750
01:08:34,870 --> 01:08:39,832
Well, when my mother was an intern,
she used to work late through the night,

751
01:08:39,916 --> 01:08:42,460
sleep through the day.

752
01:08:42,544 --> 01:08:44,378
So the only time that we ever got
to talk about anything

753
01:08:44,463 --> 01:08:45,921
was when she'd get home.

754
01:08:46,006 --> 01:08:48,549
So what I used to do,
I used to lie in my bed

755
01:08:48,633 --> 01:08:50,134
and try to stay awake as long as I could,

756
01:08:50,218 --> 01:08:53,971
but it never worked
'cause the harder I tried,

757
01:08:54,056 --> 01:08:56,265
the faster I'd fall asleep.

758
01:08:57,642 --> 01:08:59,477
Yeah. Well, that wouldn't have
mattered none in my house.

759
01:08:59,561 --> 01:09:01,854
My ma, she would've come home,
shook me awake,

760
01:09:01,938 --> 01:09:03,773
chatted me up till dawn.

761
01:09:04,232 --> 01:09:06,400
I swear, that woman
was never too tired to talk.

762
01:09:06,485 --> 01:09:10,488
Yeah. That's probably the only time
she could get a word in.

763
01:09:14,534 --> 01:09:18,079
Funny thing is,
sometimes she'd come home early,

764
01:09:18,163 --> 01:09:20,831
and I'd pretend to be asleep.

765
01:09:20,916 --> 01:09:24,543
- Who? Your mum?
- Yeah.

766
01:09:27,255 --> 01:09:30,257
She'd stand in the doorway,
looking at me.

767
01:09:30,717 --> 01:09:33,135
And I'd just keep my eyes shut.

768
01:09:35,931 --> 01:09:39,517
And I knew she just wanted
to find out about my day,

769
01:09:40,102 --> 01:09:42,561
that she came home early

770
01:09:43,980 --> 01:09:45,940
just to talk to me.

771
01:09:49,152 --> 01:09:53,364
And I still wouldn't move.
I'd still pretend to just be asleep.

772
01:10:00,580 --> 01:10:02,873
I don't know why I did that.

773
01:10:16,430 --> 01:10:20,015
We only got a couple of hours.
Shut up and go to sleep.

774
01:10:28,817 --> 01:10:31,652
Captain? Sir?

775
01:10:33,697 --> 01:10:35,156
Corporal?

776
01:10:40,370 --> 01:10:43,456
How you doing there? Are you all right?

777
01:10:43,623 --> 01:10:46,625
Yeah, I think this is
all good for me, sir.

778
01:10:48,044 --> 01:10:49,503
Really?

779
01:10:50,255 --> 01:10:51,755
How is that?

780
01:10:55,677 --> 01:10:58,220
"War educates the senses,"

781
01:10:58,305 --> 01:11:00,264
"calls into action the will,"

782
01:11:00,348 --> 01:11:03,058
"perfects the physical constitution,"

783
01:11:03,435 --> 01:11:06,312
"brings men into such swift
and close collision"

784
01:11:06,396 --> 01:11:09,523
"in critical moments
that man measures man."

785
01:11:09,983 --> 01:11:12,693
Yeah. Well, I guess
that's Emerson's way

786
01:11:13,153 --> 01:11:14,945
of finding the bright side.

787
01:11:15,030 --> 01:11:18,699
- You know Emerson, sir?
- I know some.

788
01:11:23,163 --> 01:11:27,208
So, where are you from, Captain?
What'd you do before the war?

789
01:11:29,211 --> 01:11:31,545
What's the pool up to?

790
01:11:34,883 --> 01:11:37,718
You know, I think it's around 300, sir.

791
01:11:38,553 --> 01:11:41,222
Well, when it gets up to 500,

792
01:11:41,306 --> 01:11:43,557
I'll give you the answers,
and we'll split the money.

793
01:11:43,642 --> 01:11:45,643
How about that?

794
01:11:45,727 --> 01:11:49,313
Well, if that's the way you feel, sir.
I feel it's my duty under your command

795
01:11:49,397 --> 01:11:53,651
to suggest that we wait
until it gets up to 1,000, sir.

796
01:11:55,362 --> 01:11:57,863
What if we don't live that long?

797
01:12:01,034 --> 01:12:04,119
- 500?
- 500 would be good, yeah.

798
01:12:04,204 --> 01:12:06,163
- Yes, sir.
- Yeah.

799
01:12:08,792 --> 01:12:11,544
- Get some sleep, Corporal.
- Yes, sir.

800
01:13:18,153 --> 01:13:20,362
Who's got sulfa powder?

801
01:13:22,741 --> 01:13:26,910
Medic! My buddy's bleeding!
He needs a tourniquet!

802
01:13:26,995 --> 01:13:28,495
- Wade.
- Yes, sir?

803
01:13:28,580 --> 01:13:30,539
- See what you can do.
- Yes, sir.

804
01:13:30,624 --> 01:13:33,959
Hold on, fellas. It won't be much longer.

805
01:13:34,127 --> 01:13:36,003
How we doing here?

806
01:13:36,630 --> 01:13:37,921
All right.

807
01:13:38,006 --> 01:13:40,549
Yeah, doing all right.
Don't worry about it.

808
01:13:40,634 --> 01:13:42,384
Doc's in town.

809
01:13:42,844 --> 01:13:43,927
It's all right. It's all right.

810
01:13:44,012 --> 01:13:45,512
Don't worry, fellas.

811
01:13:45,597 --> 01:13:48,140
The 29th Infantry's breaking through,
they'll be here soon.

812
01:13:48,224 --> 01:13:50,601
Plasma. Anybody got plasma?

813
01:13:50,685 --> 01:13:54,521
- Captain. Hey, Captain.
- Soldier, you want to fill me in?

814
01:13:54,606 --> 01:13:56,565
Yeah. Lieutenant DeWindt, sir.

815
01:13:56,650 --> 01:14:00,277
99th Troop Carrier Squadron,
carrying in 327th Glider Infantry.

816
01:14:00,362 --> 01:14:01,945
This one was mine, sir.

817
01:14:02,030 --> 01:14:03,447
- I was the pilot.
- Private?

818
01:14:03,531 --> 01:14:05,032
- Twenty-two men dead.
- Private, take care of..

819
01:14:05,116 --> 01:14:07,951
I ended up over there without a scratch.
It took my co-pilot's head right off.

820
01:14:08,036 --> 01:14:09,662
Well, where's the unit?
Who are these people?

821
01:14:09,746 --> 01:14:12,748
Well, the guys we came in with, sir,
they headed off first night.

822
01:14:12,832 --> 01:14:14,124
Haven't seen them since.

823
01:14:14,209 --> 01:14:18,253
Meantime, other guys keep showing up,
one, two, half-dozen at a time.

824
01:14:18,338 --> 01:14:21,131
Then some officer'll come along
and patch together a mixed unit,

825
01:14:21,216 --> 01:14:23,676
- head off to make trouble, sir.
- Water. I need a canteen over here.

826
01:14:23,760 --> 01:14:25,761
We're looking for a Private James Ryan.

827
01:14:25,845 --> 01:14:28,097
He's in Baker Company,
the 506 of the 101 st.

828
01:14:28,181 --> 01:14:30,516
No, you got me, sir.
A lot of guys come in and out of here.

829
01:14:30,600 --> 01:14:32,059
- Upham.
- Yes, sir.

830
01:14:32,143 --> 01:14:33,977
Check out that squad.
See if Ryan's in it.

831
01:14:34,062 --> 01:14:35,729
Yes, sir.

832
01:14:37,107 --> 01:14:38,565
Reiben.

833
01:14:39,067 --> 01:14:43,112
Smell that leg right there.
Find out if it's south of cheese.

834
01:14:48,743 --> 01:14:50,077
What?

835
01:14:55,542 --> 01:14:56,917
Keep moving.

836
01:14:57,001 --> 01:14:58,877
Keep moving!

837
01:14:59,796 --> 01:15:02,172
I'm Juden, you know?

838
01:15:04,426 --> 01:15:07,010
Yeah, I couldn't pry him out of there,
hard as I tried.

839
01:15:07,095 --> 01:15:09,304
- I'd need a winch.
- Yeah.

840
01:15:13,435 --> 01:15:14,727
Stars.

841
01:15:15,103 --> 01:15:19,648
Yep, Brigadier General Amend,
Deputy Commander, 101 st.

842
01:15:20,483 --> 01:15:23,026
Some fucking genius had the great idea

843
01:15:23,111 --> 01:15:24,653
of welding a couple of steel plates

844
01:15:24,738 --> 01:15:28,031
onto our deck to keep
the general safe from ground fire.

845
01:15:28,116 --> 01:15:29,700
Unfortunately,
they forgot to tell me about it

846
01:15:29,784 --> 01:15:32,202
until we were just getting airborne.

847
01:15:32,287 --> 01:15:35,289
Well, that's like trying
to fly a freight train. Okay.

848
01:15:35,915 --> 01:15:39,293
Gross overload.
Trim characteristics all shot to hell.

849
01:15:39,669 --> 01:15:42,671
I nearly broke both my arms
trying to keep her level.

850
01:15:42,756 --> 01:15:44,882
And when we released,

851
01:15:44,966 --> 01:15:47,259
you know, I cut as hard as I could,

852
01:15:47,343 --> 01:15:50,846
tried to gain some altitude
and still keep her from stalling.

853
01:15:50,930 --> 01:15:55,100
We came down like a fucking meteor.
And this is how we ended up.

854
01:15:57,270 --> 01:16:00,564
And the others, they stopped easy
enough okay though, you know?

855
01:16:00,648 --> 01:16:04,401
We were just.. We were just
too damn heavy, you know?

856
01:16:04,486 --> 01:16:06,320
The grass was wet.

857
01:16:07,155 --> 01:16:09,281
Downward slope and all.

858
01:16:09,991 --> 01:16:11,909
Twenty-two guys dead.

859
01:16:14,704 --> 01:16:18,207
- All that for a general?
- One man.

860
01:16:20,502 --> 01:16:23,754
- A lot of that going around.
- FUBAR.

861
01:16:24,339 --> 01:16:26,340
- FUBAR.
- FUBAR.

862
01:16:27,091 --> 01:16:28,509
FUBAR.

863
01:16:28,593 --> 01:16:30,719
You all got that right.

864
01:16:31,221 --> 01:16:33,138
Hey, I looked up "FUBAR"
in the German dictionary.

865
01:16:33,223 --> 01:16:34,264
There's no "FUBAR" in there.

866
01:16:34,349 --> 01:16:35,599
- Upham.
- Yes, sir?

867
01:16:35,683 --> 01:16:38,268
There's more paratroops out there.
Find out if one of them is Ryan.

868
01:16:38,353 --> 01:16:39,770
Yes, sir.

869
01:16:39,854 --> 01:16:42,523
Oh, you might want
to check these out, sir.

870
01:16:42,607 --> 01:16:44,149
Dog tags.

871
01:16:44,234 --> 01:16:47,152
More than I really want to count, sir.

872
01:16:48,363 --> 01:16:51,198
I've covered a lot of bodies, sir.

873
01:16:51,366 --> 01:16:52,741
Jackson.

874
01:16:53,368 --> 01:16:56,203
- Start going through those.
- Yes, sir.

875
01:16:57,455 --> 01:16:59,039
I'll help.

876
01:17:01,251 --> 01:17:03,794
What do you think, Jackson?
Do you think that little prick's in there?

877
01:17:03,878 --> 01:17:06,880
Well, if he is, I'm gonna find him.
I bet that son of a bitch is here.

878
01:17:06,965 --> 01:17:08,882
I got big money saying
this guy's still alive.

879
01:17:08,967 --> 01:17:11,093
10 bucks says I nail him first.

880
01:17:11,177 --> 01:17:13,804
- Let's see who we got in here.
- You mugs don't stand a chance.

881
01:17:13,888 --> 01:17:15,764
All right, you think this little
shit bird is in here or what?

882
01:17:15,849 --> 01:17:17,558
Just keep looking.

883
01:17:18,017 --> 01:17:20,185
All right. Gary lanico.

884
01:17:20,270 --> 01:17:22,062
Ben Rubino. Mike Cessacchio.

885
01:17:22,146 --> 01:17:23,939
I swear.
All the guineas are buying it, huh?

886
01:17:24,023 --> 01:17:25,816
Oh, come on, not the right name.

887
01:17:25,900 --> 01:17:28,902
Wee Willie Winkie,
that's a buddy of yours.

888
01:17:29,153 --> 01:17:31,530
We gotta find this prick.

889
01:17:35,869 --> 01:17:37,703
Where is this son of a bitch?

890
01:17:37,787 --> 01:17:40,330
Don't mix them up, Jackson, all right?
Keep them in your own fucking pile.

891
01:17:40,415 --> 01:17:42,749
How am I supposed to know
who we got?

892
01:17:42,834 --> 01:17:45,502
Why don't you just shut up,
Reiben? All right.

893
01:17:45,587 --> 01:17:49,089
- Everybody be friends.
- Cranky there, huh?

894
01:17:50,216 --> 01:17:53,010
- I think I got a winner.
- What you talking about?

895
01:17:53,094 --> 01:17:54,553
Ryan.

896
01:17:54,762 --> 01:17:57,347
- Ryan.
- Take a look at that, Mellish.

897
01:17:57,891 --> 01:17:59,182
You know what?
You're a genius. You really are.

898
01:17:59,267 --> 01:18:01,101
R-I-E-N-N-E.

899
01:18:01,185 --> 01:18:03,145
That's Rienne and that's French.
All right.

900
01:18:03,229 --> 01:18:05,314
- You know what that means?
- It means nothing.

901
01:18:05,398 --> 01:18:07,357
- What beats three of a kind?
- I got shit here.

902
01:18:07,442 --> 01:18:11,153
- I got all guys from New York.
- I got a full house.

903
01:18:11,237 --> 01:18:13,363
- Do you need a hand with that?
- I got a full house.

904
01:18:13,448 --> 01:18:14,729
I got you beat. I got
the straight flush.

905
01:18:14,742 --> 01:18:16,033
Full house, he's got.

906
01:18:16,117 --> 01:18:19,494
You were looking at my tags.
You're cheating, you know?

907
01:18:19,579 --> 01:18:21,705
- Ryan.
- Fucking unreal, this guy.

908
01:18:21,789 --> 01:18:24,374
Do you need a hand with that?
Can you read that shit?

909
01:18:24,459 --> 01:18:27,044
Jesus Christ. Look at this poor bastard.

910
01:18:27,128 --> 01:18:30,213
- I guess they're not bullet-proof, huh?
- Guess not. All right?

911
01:18:30,298 --> 01:18:31,715
I don't like
what he's got between his ears.

912
01:18:31,799 --> 01:18:34,718
Sort of like what you fellas got
between your legs.

913
01:18:34,802 --> 01:18:36,887
- We got to give him that.
- That's not bad.

914
01:18:36,971 --> 01:18:38,472
Not bad with you, Jackson.

915
01:18:38,556 --> 01:18:40,557
All right, I got three of a kind.
All right.

916
01:18:40,642 --> 01:18:41,808
- Full house.
- What the hell are you doing?

917
01:18:41,893 --> 01:18:44,394
The whole goddamn
Airborne's watching.

918
01:18:44,479 --> 01:18:45,938
These aren't poker chips.

919
01:18:46,022 --> 01:18:49,858
- All right, all right, all right.
- Put them back in there!

920
01:19:13,383 --> 01:19:15,050
He's not here.

921
01:19:19,514 --> 01:19:21,890
Maybe we should bust up
into a couple of different groups, huh?

922
01:19:22,016 --> 01:19:23,225
And wander the woods
like Hansel and Gretel,

923
01:19:23,351 --> 01:19:24,393
calling his name.

924
01:19:24,519 --> 01:19:27,646
He's bound to hear us sooner
or later. Ryan!

925
01:19:27,730 --> 01:19:30,899
That might be
a little hard to do, Captain.

926
01:19:31,609 --> 01:19:34,861
Maybe the locals have seen him.
Hey, you know..

927
01:19:38,199 --> 01:19:40,701
Ryan! Anybody know Ryan,
101 st Airborne?

928
01:19:40,785 --> 01:19:44,579
Ryan? You know a guy named Ryan?
Private James Ryan from Iowa?

929
01:19:44,706 --> 01:19:46,707
Anybody know a Ryan?

930
01:19:47,208 --> 01:19:49,126
James Ryan!

931
01:19:49,210 --> 01:19:55,173
Hey, Joe, doesn't Mandelsohn pal
around with a Ryan from C Company?

932
01:19:55,258 --> 01:19:58,552
- Yeah. I think so.
- Bring him up here, would you?

933
01:20:07,895 --> 01:20:10,439
- Do you know Private Ryan?
- You're gonna have to speak up, sir.

934
01:20:10,565 --> 01:20:11,732
You're gonna have to speak up, sir.

935
01:20:11,816 --> 01:20:13,483
- My hearing is not good!
- It comes and goes!

936
01:20:13,568 --> 01:20:14,776
- It comes and goes!
- A German grenade went off

937
01:20:14,902 --> 01:20:16,695
- next to his ear.
- A grenade went off right by my head!

938
01:20:16,779 --> 01:20:19,823
Got it, got it. Do you know Private Ryan?

939
01:20:19,907 --> 01:20:21,366
Who?

940
01:20:21,451 --> 01:20:23,910
Private Ryan! James Ryan!

941
01:20:23,995 --> 01:20:28,206
- Jimmy Ryan?
- James! James Francis Ryan!

942
01:20:28,291 --> 01:20:32,127
- No, no, no. James Francis Ryan.
- All right. Get me a pencil.

943
01:20:32,253 --> 01:20:34,546
Something to write on.
Something to write on.

944
01:20:34,630 --> 01:20:37,132
Quick! Quick! Come on, a pencil!

945
01:20:38,926 --> 01:20:40,677
A small one, sir.

946
01:20:41,304 --> 01:20:42,429
Write this down.

947
01:20:42,513 --> 01:20:44,473
James Francis Ryan, question mark.

948
01:20:44,599 --> 01:20:46,349
Iowa, question mark.

949
01:20:46,434 --> 01:20:48,935
Do you know him? Does he know him?

950
01:20:49,020 --> 01:20:51,104
Read the message. Look.

951
01:20:52,940 --> 01:20:56,943
- Yeah. Of course I know him, sir.
- Does he know where he is?

952
01:21:00,782 --> 01:21:04,159
Yeah, yeah. We missed
our drop zone by about 20 miles,

953
01:21:04,285 --> 01:21:07,579
ended up way over
by Bumville or some damn place.

954
01:21:07,663 --> 01:21:10,791
Him, me and a couple of other guys
were coming here to the rally point,

955
01:21:10,875 --> 01:21:16,046
ran into a Colonel who was gathering
up men to go to Ramelle.

956
01:21:16,380 --> 01:21:17,464
Ramelle.

957
01:21:17,548 --> 01:21:20,008
To baby-sit a bridge.
That's the last I've seen of him, sir.

958
01:21:20,134 --> 01:21:22,010
Great! Great! Thank you.

959
01:21:22,136 --> 01:21:24,387
Write thank.. Read, and thank you.

960
01:21:24,472 --> 01:21:26,973
- You're welcome!
- Assemble on me.

961
01:21:29,143 --> 01:21:31,144
Thank you, Lieutenant.

962
01:21:33,731 --> 01:21:35,148
Ramelle.

963
01:21:36,692 --> 01:21:38,860
We're here. There.

964
01:21:39,320 --> 01:21:44,574
Ramelle is on the Merderet River,
right here, just to the southwest of us.

965
01:21:44,659 --> 01:21:47,035
You know anything about this bridge
